9️⃣ Custom Resources (CR)
Operators are controlled through Custom Resources (CR).
A Custom Resource defines what application instance to deploy.
Example:
Create a MySQL database.
CR Example YAML:
apiVersion: mysql.example.com/v1
kind: MySQL
metadata:
  name: mydatabase
spec:
  storage: 10Gi
  version: 8.0
Operator reads this and automatically:
•	Creates pods
•	Creates storage
•	Configures database
________________________________________
Create CR via Web Console
Go to:
Operators → Installed Operators → Operator → Custom Resource tab
Click
Create
You can use:
YAML View
Write full YAML.
________________________________________
Form View
Fill fields like form.
Example fields:
•	database size
•	version
•	replicas
